  <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Design and Testing of Crowbar Protection System for the JT-60SA Superconducting Magnet Power Supplies</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="260" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="c">2017-03-13</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">• The Crowbar System is a key protection system for the Super Conducting Magnet Power Supplies (SCMPSs). • It is a Safety Relevant component and it is designed to be seismic resistant. • The Crowbar System has to carry the current flowing through superconducting coils, during faults or plasma disruptions, even in case of earthquake events. • The over-voltages protection is performed by a voltage transducer, a Break-Over-Diode and a varistor. • The full current tests performed on Crowbar have confirmed the goodness of design. • Seismic tests of Crowbar did not highlight any problem in the design. • The adopted technical choices for Crowbar design assure a fast intervention and a high redundancy protection level.</subfield>
